    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In n(omine) Patris et Filii et Spiritus Sancti. Anno Deo propicio
                        pontificatus domni nostri <persName key="#Popes" ref="#people/266"
                            >Benedicti</persName> summi <rs key="#Popes">pontificis</rs> et
                        universalis pape in apostolica sacratissima beati Petri apostoli Domini sede
                        tercio sitque imperante domno piissimo perpetuo augusto <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/130">Heinricus</persName> a Deo
                        coronato pacifico magno <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperatore</rs> in Italia
                        anno secundo, die tercio mense decemb(er), indicione terciadecima,
                            <placeName ref="#places/485">Cumiaclo</placeName>. Ea enim que gesta
                        esse videntur ne prolixis temporibus memoriter retineri non possunt, ideo
                        scripturê vinculis annotari êquum est. Igitur cum Christi auxilio dum
                        resideret in iudicio et in generali placito domnus <persName
                            key="#Count #Other_palatine_officer"><name ref="Nanno"
                            >Nannone</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs> et <rs key="#Other_palatine_officer"
                            >camararius</rs> domni Heinrici imperatoris in <rs key="#Houses"
                            >mansione</rs> de <persName key="#Houses"><name
                                ref="Vitalis de Gaudiosa">Vitale de Gaudiosa</name></persName> et
                        cum e[o tam] residentium quamque adstancium fulti nobilitatis pollentibus et
                        bone opinionis et laudabilis fama viri, quorum nomina h[ec sunt]: idest in
                        primis <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Alfredus"
                            >Alfredus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Witness #Judge">iudex</rs> et <persName key="#Witness #Judge"
                                ><name ref="Martinus">Martinus</name></persName> iudex de <placeName
                            ref="#places/65">Papia</placeName> et <persName key="#Witness #Judge"
                                ><name ref="Martinus">Martinus</name></persName> iudex <placeName
                            ref="#places/80">Ferr(ariensis)</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Sichelmus">Sichelmus</name></persName>
                        iudex, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name ref="Gherarus"
                            >Gariardus</name></persName> iudex de <placeName ref="#places/77"
                            >Ficari[olo]</placeName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Everardus">Verardus</name></persName> iudex de <placeName
                            ref="#places/3521">Copario</placeName>, <persName key="Witness"
                            ref="#people/1573">Gerardus</persName> dativus de
                            <placeName>Faroaldo</placeName>, <persName key="#Witness #Judge"><name
                                ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName> iudex de Cumiaclo, <persName
                            key="Witness"><name ref="Romualdus">Romualdus</name></persName> et
                            <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Lucius">Liucio</name></persName>
                        germani filii quondam <persName key="#Marquis/duke"><name ref="Heinricus"
                                >[Hein]ricis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Marquis/duke">ex genere ducis</rs>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Toresindus">Torisindo</name></persName> filio <persName><name
                                ref="Federicus">Fredericus</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="Witness"><name ref="Petrus/Hugo">Petrus qui vocatur
                            Ugo</name></persName> filio quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Petrus de Christinduli">Petri de Christiduli</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Amelricus"
                            >Almericus</name></persName> de Ferraria, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Guarinus">Guarino</name></persName> filio quond[am]
                                <persName><name ref="Adalardus">Adelardi</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Mancio">Mango</name></persName> de
                        Ferraria, <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Martinus Francus">Martinus
                                Franco</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Raginelmus">Raginelmo</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="Witness"><name ref="Gotefredus">Gotifredus</name></persName> de
                            <placeName ref="#places/7">Bononia</placeName>, <persName key="Witness"
                                ><name ref="Leo">Leo</name></persName> filio quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Petrus de Blata">Petri de Blata</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="Witness"><name ref="Everardus">Verardus</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName>
                        filio <persName><name ref="Andreas de Gazio">Andrea de
                            Gazio</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Paulus de Argiale">Paulo qui vocatur de
                            Argiale</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Adalbertus de Romulado">Adelbertus de
                            Romuald(o)</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Bonaldus">Bonaldo</name></persName> de Cumiaclo, <persName
                            key="Witness"><name ref="Dominicus Strambo">Dominicus
                            Strambo</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Iohannes Calegarius">Iohannes Calegario</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="Leo"><name ref="Leo">Leo</name></persName> de <placeName
                            ref="#places/3529">Rere</placeName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName> genero suo, <persName
                            key="Witness"><name ref="Leo de Rainerius">Leo de
                            Rainerio</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Petrus Arnadorso">Petrus Arnadorso</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Witness #Other_clerics"><name ref="Stephanus de Iohannes"
                                >Stephanus de Ioh(anne)s</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clericus</rs>, <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Everardus"
                                >Verardus</name></persName> gener quondam <persName><name
                                ref="Dominicus Tinca">Dominicus Tinca</name></persName>,
                                <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Martinus/Storto">Martinus qui vocatur
                                Storto</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Dominicus Ricio"
                                >Dominicus Ricio</name></persName>, <persName key="Witness"><name
                                ref="Iohannes Zadarino">Iohannes Zadarino</name></persName>,
                        <persName key="#Witness #Chancellor"><name ref="Guarinus"
                            >Guarino</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancell(arius)</rs>, <persName key="Witness"><name ref="Honestus"
                                >Aunesto</name></persName> preconario et me presente <persName
                            key="#Tabellio" ref="#people/1575">Lopicinus</persName> in Dei nomine
                            <rs key="#Tabellio">tabellio</rs> et aliis plures quê longum est
                        adscribendum; in nostrorum suprascriptorum omnium presentia accedens domnus
                            <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1574">Uuido</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Churches #Monasteries #Abbots"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1460">sanctê <placeName
                                key="#Imperial/royal_diploma #Landed_possessions #Fisheries #Fiscal_property #Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities #Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium #Churches #Monasteries #Abbots"
                                ref="#places/4179">Pomposiane</placeName> êcclesiê</orgName> et
                        ostendit ibi <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">preceptum</rs> unum ubi
                        continebantur locum unum qui dicitur <placeName ref="#places/3559"
                            key="#Fiscal_property"><geogName ref="#estates/2454"
                                key="#Fiscal_property">Laco</geogName></placeName> et <rs
                            key="#Fisheries">piscaria</rs> una qui dicitur <geogName
                            key="#Fisheries #Fiscal_property" ref="#estates/2455"><placeName
                                key="#Fisheries #Fiscal_property">Tidini</placeName></geogName> et
                        locum unum qui dicitur <placeName ref="#places/3561" key="#Fiscal_property"
                            >Montone Lasisico</placeName> et omnibus rebus quanta ab ipso Laco
                        Sancto pertinet et dixit quod si aliqua persona esset que adversum illum
                        preceptum aliquid contrarietatis dicere vellet, paratus esset cum eo litem
                        legaliter finire; et neminem invenit qui adversus eundem preceptum
                        contrarius existeret. Et cum taliter suprascripti iudices vidissent et
                        audissent, dixerunt rectum esse ut prefatus domnus comes eundem abbatem cum
                        vocatore suo nomine <persName key="#Tabellio"><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Petro</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Tabellio">tabell(ione)</rs> de suprascriptis omnibus re[bus iuxta]
                        predictum preceptum investiret et in <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">C
                            mancosos aureos eos bandiret</rs>. Tunc ipse domnus Nanno comes per
                        fustem, quê suis tenebat man[ibus, predictum] abbatem cum prenominato <rs
                            key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities">advocato</rs> suo de
                        suprascriptis omnibus rebus iuxta predictum preceptum eos investivit et
                        bannum domni imperatoris super eos mi[sit ut], si aliqua persona esset que
                        prenominato Pomposiano <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs> vel eidem
                        domni abbati aut suis successoribus sine legale iudicio contrario existeret,
                        C [mancosos] aureos componere, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis">camere
                            predicti domni imperatoris</rs> et medietatem <rs
                            key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities">predicto monasterio</rs>. Et
                        statim apprehendit publicum can[cellarium nomine] Guarino et misit in manum
                        predicti domni abbatis ut cum eo ad suprascriptis rebus pergeret et eum inde
                        investiret in perpetuum. Hoc factum est sub die et mense [et indicione]
                        suprascripta terciadecima, in Cumiaclo. Signum manibus meis
                        s(uprascrip)t(us) domnus Nanno comes et camararius domni Heinrici
                        imperatoris in hac breve ut sup(erius) l(egitur) et blandivi ad omnia
                        suprascripta cui relectum est. Martinus iudex apostolicê sedis et sacri
                        palatii interfuit. Alfredus iudex sacri palatii interfui et subscripsi.
                        Martinus iudex Ferr(ariensis) interfui et subscripsi. Petrus Dei gratia
                        iudex Cummiaclensis interfui et subscripsi. Sichelmus iudex sacri palacii
                        interfui et subscripsi. Gariardus iudex sacri palacii interfui et
                        subscripsi. Everardus missus ibi fui et subscripsi.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
